ca.ualberta.t14.gametrader

Class ObjParseSingleton

  • java.lang.Object
    • ca.ualberta.t14.gametrader.ObjParseSingleton

  • public class ObjParseSingleton
extends java.lang.Object
    This optimistic singleton provides global access to a object holder that can accept and hold objects, and give them back at a later time given a keyword. Intended to be used to pass along objects from one Activity to another.

      • getObject

        public java.lang.Object getObject(java.lang.String idName)
        Retrieves an object from the singleton data holder with given keyword. If no such keyword exist, returned object is null! If exist object will be returned and the keyword & object pair will NOT be removed from this singleton data holder. So the keyword & object pair continue to exist in the singleton data holder.
        Parameters:
        idName - the keyword to find the object.
        Returns:
        the object associated o the keyword.
